fields.description:
*About Kanban*

[Kanban|http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kanban_(development)] is part of the Toyota Lean Manufacturing methodology but was popularised for use in IT by David Anderson. Broadly speaking it aims to optimize outcomes by: 
  - Prioritizing items that are added to the potential work list then only commencing work on items when capacity exists to take them on 
  - Tracking items in progress so that items that have started are completed before new work is taken on 
  - Ensuring that items that are in progress do not get blocked indefinitely at any particular stage of the work 

You can check out many Kanban resources at http://agilemanagement.net/

*To close this view of this task (called the Detail view), click the cross in the top right corner*
fields.summary: Kanban cards represent work items >> Click the "TES-1" link at the top of this card to show the Detail view - there's more on Kanban in the 'Description' section

fields.description:
*To delete this Sample Project _(must be performed by a user with Administration rights)_* 
- Open the administration interface to the projects page by using the keyboard shortcut 'g' then 'g' and typing 'Projects' in to the search dialog
- Select the "Delete" link for the "TestProject" project

*To delete the Sample Project workflow and workflow scheme _(must be performed by a user with Administration rights)_* 
- Open the administration interface to the workflow schemes page by using the keyboard shortcut 'g' then 'g' and typing 'Workflow Schemes' in to the search dialog
- Select the "Delete" link for the "TES: Agile Simplified Workflow Scheme" workflow scheme
- Go to the workflows page by using the keyboard shortcut 'g' then 'g' and typing 'Workflows' in to the search dialog(_OnDemand users should select the second match for Workflows_)
- Expand the "Inactive" section
- Select the "Delete" link for the "Agile Simplified Workflow  for Project TES" workflow

*To delete this Board _(must be performed by the owner of this Board or an Administrator)_*
- Click the "Tools" cog at the top right of this board
- Select "Delete"
fields.summary: Instructions for deleting this sample board and project are in the description for this issue >> Click the "TES-10" link and read the description tab of the detail view for more
